Tavatron tore into the soft blue scales of the fish, her fangs easily 
ripping it in two. Tavatron's wolfen teeth easily ground the soft bones into 
a sand-like state. Tavatron swallowed, her appetite finally appeased. She 
tossed the remainder of the fish into the bushes, by now it had been reduced 
to nothing more than a small section of spine and a large blue tail.

Tavatron licked her fangs, wishing she had time to do more fishing. Tavatron 
instinctively shook her head, trying to remove the majority of water from 
her soaked fur, with little success. Still dripping she sighed, she didn't 
wear water well.

Tavatron perked her ears at the sound of breaking bones and ripping flesh. 
She gave Dinobot an inquisitive look before tuning to head out of the 
forest. They had better hurry, Prowl had ordered them back to base a while 
ago, and now Iron Raptor had notified her to return, perhaps there was a 
situation back at base they was not aware of. If so it could prove best if 
they hurried:

"Iron Raptor sounded... odd when she spoke. If you don't object I would feel 
better if we ran back to base." Tavatron didn't wait for a reply, something 
was up, she knew it. She took one last look at Dinobot then bolted out of 
the forest towards the ark, making sure to keep her pace one that Dinobot 
could easily catch up with.
